The paper discusses a deep learning approach for spatiotemporal correlation in video data, specifically for action recognition. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions multimodal fusion, which involves combining different types of data, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of fully connected layers suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
